cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.AI 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques for patient phenotyping, which is a classification task for determining whether a patient has a medical condition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also uses deep learning algorithms, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The use of healthcare data and clinical notes suggests cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with classification tasks, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
